# A merge in which the same file is changed differently on both branches
# produces a conflict.
I definitions.inc
> init
<<<
+ f.txt conflict1.txt
> add f.txt
<<<
> commit "base f"
<<<
> branch other
<<<
+ f.txt wug.txt
> add f.txt
<<<
> commit "master changes f"
<<<
> checkout other
<<<
+ f.txt notwug.txt
> add f.txt
<<<
> commit "other changes f"
<<<
> checkout master
<<<
> merge other
Encountered a merge conflict.
<<<
# The merge auto-commits the conflict resolution, so nothing stays staged.
> status
=== Branches ===
\*master
other

=== Staged Files ===

=== Removed Files ===

=== Modifications Not Staged For Commit ===

